reviewText: Least entertaining of the Kane DVDs (except for the commercials).  Includes a less-than-stellar portrayal of Kane by Mark Stevens.  Also contains two superior William Gargan episodes, but one is a renamed show from Vol. 1 (about the lady "psychic").  Completists will want this DVD, however.
If you are into nostalgic film this is for you. I enjoyed this as much or more than I did when I was a kid and first saw them. Several short 1/2 hour films.
